CLARK THOUGHT HIS FAMILY WAS RICH AS A CHILD.
CLARK FATHERS WAS A CUSTODIAN IN A LIBRARY.
AT NIGHT WHEN THE LIBRARY CLOSED, MR.
CLARK WOULD RUN AROUND THE LIBRARY AND COULD MAKE AS MUCH NOISE AS HE WANTED.
CLARK WOULD STAY UP UNTIL 3 IN THE MORNING READING BOOKS.
WHENEVER HE WANTED AN ANSWER TO SOMETHING, HE WOULD GO TO THE LIBRARY AND FIND THE ANSWER.
NO ON IN HIS FAMILY HAD GRADUATED OR GONE TO COLLEGE.
HIS DAD WOULD WAX THE FLOORS AND THE TOP OF THE BOOKSTACKS UNTIL THEY GLEAMED.
HIS FRIENDS NEVER CAME TO WHERE HE LIVED BECAUSE HE DIDN’T TELL THEM HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
HIS FATHER WORKED IN A LIBRARY AND ALSO HIS FAMILY LIVED THERE.
HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICH GROWING UP.
HE WOULD GO TO THE LIBRARY AT NIGHT AND READ UNTIL 3 AM.
NO ONE IN HIS FAMILY WENT TO COLLEGE.
HE HAD A THIRST FOR KNOWLEDGE.
HIS FATHER WOULD WAX THE TOP OF THE BOOK STACKS UNTIL THEY GLEAMED.
